  "repo_truth": "Five fresh HCM-0.8 reviews returned Required findings. The active parent remediated all rounds. The latest repair makes PG-HANDOFF-01 conditionally close on the validated v1.2 parent record, records PG-ORCH-01 proof with final lineage owned by that record, and records PG-ORCH-02 as proven while leaving PG-HANDOFF-02 open. This manifest binds the complete current dirty documentation/control-plane subject; no Rust paths are included.",
  "allowed_scope": [
    "Read every path in subject_manifest and the five prior immutable HCM-0.8 review dispatches.",
    "Run read-only schema, semantic-lineage, proof-state, multi-round remediation, primary-commit identity, two-commit baseline replay, delegation-capability, history-admission, ledger, link, portability, archive, docs-only, and whitespace checks.",
    "Return findings only; do not edit, commit, create a handoff, append the ledger, or create another dispatch."
  ],
  "non_goals": [
    "No Rust or runtime implementation.",
    "No edits to immutable records or dispatches.",
    "No reuse of any prior reviewer or its conclusions as authority.",
    "No global handoff, ledger write, or user task hop by the reviewer."
  ],
  "tasks": [
    "Independently review the complete five-times-remediated subject without relying on the parent success claim.",
    "Retest every prior Required finding and verify the three corrected proof-gate state cells are truthful before and after the conditional v1.2 closeout; PG-HANDOFF-02 must remain open.",
    "Verify one active parent still owns HCM-0.8 and all coupled documents, schemas, templates, and validator behavior agree.",
    "Replay this subject manifest, run the full proof wall, and return findings first with severity, file/line, contract/gate, smallest remediation, and missing proof."
  ],
  "contracts_and_gates": [
    "05 Development orchestration contracts",
    "06 PG-HANDOFF-01",
    "06 PG-HANDOFF-02",
    "06 PG-ORCH-01",
    "06 PG-ORCH-02",
